postcontent: For all you discriminating Tommygunners out there....Here's a nice WWII Thompson drum pouch with strap and all hardware intact.This one was used but is in pretty decent shape, stitching is in good condition, snap works fine and the strap, although a bit frayed in one spot and having a few small rust spots, is in good solid shape too.This one is faintly marked "U.S." on the outside of the cover and inside, the maker mark is "BOYLE", also faint but readable.The pouch was stiff and hard with salt, but probably not from sweat as it was soaked in evenly over the entire pouch as if immersed in saltwater (or sea water), so may have been used in a beach landing or?? title: For Sale:  S&W pre-Model 10 / Victory WW2 era
postcontent: I've got a S&W pre-Model 10 / Victory model. 6 shot cylinder. The Model 10 came out in the mid/late 50s and these were sent to the British during WW2. There is no S&W stamp on it which is common according to my research. The production date is between 1940 and 1945. This is similar to the handgun used by Lee Harvey Oswald, ordered through the mail, to shoot Dallas policeman J. D. Tippit during the JFK assassination. Original grips from what I've been told and possible the barrel was cut/coverted when we sent the handguns over to the British or when they were sent on the US surplus market during the 50s and 60s which the conversion from 38 S&W to 38 Special was completed. $350 cash, firm, and not interested in trades. title: For Sale:  M1 Garand Springfield Sept. 1942 CMP Special Mint w/extras- ammo, parts, bayonet, etc.
postcontent:
Well here's one of my prized possessions up for sale. Financial situation requires it. This is a CMP Special Grade M1 Garand rifle. Serial #837xxx puts it at a September 1942 production at the Springfield Armory in MA. so plenty early to have seen lots of action. Rebuilt by CMP armorers with new barrel, stock set, springs and other parts as needed. Has not been fired since I bought it from CMP 2 years ago. I personally applied 3 coats of Tom’s 1/3 Mix (Natural Beeswax, Mineral Spirits and Boiled Linseed Oil) over a period of several weeks back when I first acquired it. Stock is a real beauty and now ready for any weather thrown at it. Steel Parkerizing is 100%. These have been sold out for some time and as CMP's supply of Garands has dried up so maybe never to be seen again. Lots of extras included-
500 rounds of Prvi Partizan 30-06 Springfield (M1 Garand) 150 Grain Full Metal Jacket (currently going for $420 + ship at Midway USA). Good stuff loaded to M2 Ball specs.
20 rounds Hornady 30-06 Springfield 168 gr. A-Max M1 Garand ammo. Hunting or match use.
UFH (Universal Fork and Hoe) mint condition bayonet and scabbard- WW II original not a cheap knock off. In this shape these go for $150-$200+ on Ebay.
51 eight round clips made by AEC- all mint cond. New production, AEC was an original WW II clip contractor.
3 five round clips for hunting use.
5 bandoleers w/cardboard inserts.
Wolff Repair Kit with springs/parts most likely to wear/get lost on an M1.
Complete GI cleaning kit is stored in the buttstock storage compartments.
GI web sling- mint
Canvas weapon storage bag for M1
CMP hard case
Books- both mint- "The M1 Garand Owner’s Guide" and "The US M1 Garand Rifle in Pictures- WW II and Korea".
Certificate of authenticity, hang tag and other CMP docs.
$1575 for all. No trades please- need cash or I'd never be selling this. Face to face in Montana (I'll drive halfway for a serious buyer) to an adult Montana resident willing to sign a bill of sale. Thanks for looking and feel free to ask any questions you may have.
